    "name": "Nehemiah (4)",
    "profile": "An American metalcore band from Minneapolis, Minnesota. The band heavily implemented black and death metal sounds into their repertoire. They were active as a full time band from 2000-2005, releasing an LP, \"The Asphyxiation Process\", in 2003, and an EP, \"Lenore\", in 2005, both through Uprising Records. The band embarked on multiple tours with bands like A Perfect Murder, Cast From Eden, Coma Eternal, Too Pure To Die, With Dead Hands Rising, and more. The band has reunited for several shows since breaking up, including two Midwest Meltdown reunion-based mini-fests in 2018.\r\n\r\nNehemiah was:\r\nLogan Kelly - Lead guitar\r\nSteve Klingler - Drums\r\nEvan Nagan - Vocals\r\nBraden Wise - Vocals\r\nChad Fjerstad - Bass\r\nJosh Lutterman - Guitars",
